{"schema":"allo-reading-book@1","slug":"329920-when-we-are-home","title":"When We Are Home","description":"Home is the sights, the sounds, the smells and the touch of every room. In this book, Moromi remembers her home that was displaced by a flood.","language":"English","langCode":"en","isRtl":false,"level":"2","orientation":"landscape","authors":["Priyadarshini Gogoi"],"illustrators":["Pankaj Saikia"],"originalAuthors":[],"publisher":"Pratham Books","license":"CC BY 4.0","licenseUrl":"https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/","sourceId":"storyweaver","contentType":"story","source":{"id":"storyweaver","name":"StoryWeaver, Pratham Books","url":"https://storyweaver.org.in/en/stories/329920-when-we-are-home"},"cover":{"card":"https://static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/426897/size3/727db468b86fe56b22b791ebcecc0a19.jpg","large":"https://static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/426897/size6/727db468b86fe56b22b791ebcecc0a19.jpg"},"audio":null,"pages":[{"n":1,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/419183/size6/88112cd3888511b852e92bdd918435ab.jpg","text":"Our home tastes like the sweet, crunchy til pitha \nthat Anaideo grinds up in the kitchen.","words":null},{"n":2,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/419188/size6/b156bb2f3a56339546b31f0836696d7b.jpg","text":"Our home sounds like Papa’s loud snores \nshaking the bedroom as he takes his afternoon nap.","words":null},{"n":3,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/419184/size6/e23ccb0942600670c06ba13c2997a0cb.jpg","text":"Our home looks like Ma weaving on the loom \nin the living room while Huntu and I wrestle.","words":null},{"n":4,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/419186/size6/bcea41be549160d6929ab3e29c051eb5.jpg","text":"Our home feels like a cool, splashy shower in the bathroom\nafter a hot, sweaty day of playing outside.","words":null},{"n":5,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/419187/size6/1e898e613df34e738fb4299c58c200bf.jpg","text":"Our home smells like kopou flowers and \nripe jackfruit as we sip tea in the courtyard.","words":null},{"n":6,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/419162/size6/f206babb6de09570fef24c0e69428f06.jpg","text":"One day, we will be home again.","words":null}],"stats":{"pages":6,"words":92}}